OL,4,CE.On compensates customers after
OL,5,CChristmas blunder
OL,6, E.On will pay more than #650,000 in
OL,7, compensation after the energy giant
OL,8, took payments from customers earlier
OL,9, than agreed, leaving some people facing
OL,10, financial difficulties over Christmas.
OL,12,FEnergy regulator Ofgem said the firm
OL,13,Ftook money from 1.6 million customers
OL,14,Fon 24 December instead of in January.
OL,16,FConsequently, customers may have
OL,17,Fexperienced "difficulty making payments
OL,18,Fin the run up to Christmas".
OL,20,FOfgem said E.On reported the problem on
OL,21,Fthe day it occurred.
